<TITLE> Iran wants economic, security pacts with Gulf Arabs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DOHA, Dec 3 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Iran's President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad told a summit of Gulf Arab heads of state on Monday that Tehran wanted to create an economic cooperation bloc and a joint security pact with them to promote peace and prosperity. Ahmadinejad was speaking to a meeting of heads of state of the Gulf Cooperation Council in Doha, Qatar. With tensions running high over Iran's nuclear ambitions, Ahmadinejad was invited to attend the summit this year. "Cooperation could make the Persian Gulf an area of peace," Ahmadinejad said in a televised speech at the start of the meeting. Most Arab countries prefer to call the region the Arabian Gulf. GCC members Saudi Arabia, Oman, the United Arab Emirates, Kuwait, Bahrain and Qatar share Western concerns about Iran's nuclear programme and some have maritime border disputes with the Islamic Republic. Iranian officials said this was the first time an Iranian president had been invited to a GCC summit. "Naturally I will present new proposals to expand cooperation and ensure regional security and I hope they will be considered by our brothers," Ahmadinejad told reporters before leaving Tehran for the summit. Iran regularly calls for a security cooperation pact with Gulf Arab states as the best way of securing the region and ridding it of US forces, a proposal Gulf Arabs have ignored. The United Arab Emirates has a long-running row with Iran over the sovereignty of three islands in the Gulf. Kuwait is also trying to resolve a maritime border dispute with the Islamic Republic blocking the development of a gas field. Ahmadinejad, who regularly rails against the United States, also said of his trip to Qatar: "It seems a new chapter has been opened in the relations between the Persian Gulf States." "Iran's definite policy is to promote broad cooperation with all countries, particularly friendly neighbouring countries." The United States, which is leading efforts to isolate Iran, accuses it of seeking to build nuclear b